To create an animated LED indicator circle from Detroit Become Human in SVG/HTML/CSS, you can follow these steps:

1. Create an SVG element in HTML to hold the LED indicator circle.
```html
<div class="led-indicator">
  <svg width="100" height="100">
    <!-- LED indicator circle SVG code will go here -->
  </svg>
</div>
```
1. Create the LED indicator circle SVG code using the following code:
```svg
<svg width="100" height="100">
  <circle cx="50" cy="50" r="30" fill="white" stroke="black" stroke-width="5" />
  <circle cx="50" cy="50" r="30" fill="white" stroke="black" stroke-width="5" />
  <circle cx="50" cy="50" r="30" fill="white" stroke="black" stroke-width="5" />
</svg>
```
This will create a circle with a white fill and a black stroke, with a radius of 30 pixels. The `cx` and `cy` coordinates are set to 50, which centers the circle within the SVG element.

1. Add CSS to animate the LED indicator circle.
```css
.led-indicator {
  animation: led-indicator 1s linear infinite;
}

@keyframes led-indicator {
  0% {
    transform: rotate(0deg);
  }
  25% {
    transform: rotate(90deg);
  }
  50% {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }
  75% {
    transform: rotate(270deg);
  }
  100% {
    transform: rotate(0deg);
  }
}
```
This CSS code will animate the LED indicator circle by rotating it 360 degrees over a period of 1 second. The `animation` property is applied to the `led-indicator` class, which is assigned to the `div` element containing the LED indicator circle.

1. Apply the CSS to the HTML file.

That's it! You now have an animated LED indicator circle from Detroit Become Human in SVG/HTML/CSS.
